Today, March 20, Haitians go to the polls to decide who will be the Caribbean
nation's next president. This runoff election is [being contested by Mirlande
Manigat and Michel Martelly](http://jamaica-
gleaner.com/gleaner/20110320/focus/focus6.html), the two candidates deemed to
have received the highest number of votes in the controversial general
election held last November. Reports posted this morning by Twitter users on
the ground in Haiti pointed to delays in the opening of polling stations,
while many outside the country fixated on an incident in which Haiti-born rap
star Wyclef Jean, a Martelly supporter, [was shot in the
hand](http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-12799421). Here's a
selection of photos posted on Twitter of the scenes in Haiti as the polls
opened—or tried to—this morning.

